Vice President Kamala Harris expresses her belief that John Fetterman will win the election in Pennsylvania. She highlights the importance of understanding what is at stake, mentioning threats to Social Security, Medicare, and national abortion. Harris emphasizes the significance of Pennsylvania as the birthplace of freedom and liberty and urges people to exercise their voting power. She praises Fetterman as a fighter for working people who understands the struggles individuals face. 

On a different note, Harris discusses an act of violence against Speaker Pelosi's home, expressing her concern about the fueled hate and division in the country. She emphasizes the need for leaders to be mindful of their words and actions, and calls for speaking out against hate and violence. Harris acknowledges the importance of public discourse but criticizes recent discourse that she finds beneath the dignity and intelligence of the American people.